name: Tempulli Wat Sri Suphan.
description: {'Information': ['Wat Sri Suphan, also known as the Silver Temple, is a unique Buddhist temple in Chiang Mai, famous for its intricate silver craftsmanship.'], 'Historical Importance': ['Built in the 16th century during the Mangrai Dynasty.', 'Serves as a spiritual and cultural center for local silversmiths.'], 'Key Features': ['Stunning handcrafted silver ordination hall (Ubosot).', 'Intricate silver reliefs depicting Buddhist teachings.', 'Workshops where artisans create silver religious artifacts.', 'Illuminated temple at night, creating a magical ambiance.'], 'Visit tips': ['Opening Hours: Daily from 6:00 AM to 9:00 PM.', 'Women are not allowed inside the main silver ordination hall.']}

name: Wat Pha Lat

short_description: A hidden jungle temple with waterfalls, stone carvings, and a peaceful meditation retreat.

name: Wat Moil Lock

name: Watchediluang Varaviharn
